imdb.title: Un-Go
imdb.plot: In a post-war Japan, an experienced detective takes on cases with the help of his supernatural assistant.

episodes.title: Murder at the Ball
episodes.plot: A corporate president under suspicion for criminal activities is found stabbed in the back at a ballroom event he was hosting.

episodes.title: Pitiless Song
episodes.plot: A wealthy woman, who used to manage a popular music band, is found murdered in a briefcase that was delivered to her home.

episodes.title: Masked Mansion
episodes.plot: Mitsuko Sasa asks Shinjuro to investigate the death of her brother Kazamori.

episodes.title: House, Unmasked
episodes.plot: Upon the revelation that Kazamori is a computer, Shinjuro must now learn who created Kazamori and why they destroyed his body.

episodes.title: The Phantom Statue
episodes.plot: At a newly unveiled memorial, two corpses are found inside a statue.

episodes.title: The Code Too Simple
episodes.plot: Yajima, a former inmate who received a mysterious coded manuscript, asks Shinjuro to help in deciphering the manuscript.

episodes.title: Daydream
episodes.plot: Shinjuro traps him in a fantasy where the war that devastated Tokyo never happened, and he is a cameraman making a film... and investigating the disappearance of his director.

episodes.title: King of Paradise
episodes.plot: Rie and Izumi are trapped in Shinjuro's fantasy. However Shinjuro is able to escape and track down the real crime, while Inga and Bettenou face off.

episodes.title: I'm Just Searching
episodes.plot: At a party hosted by the definitely alive Rinroku, Shinjuro realizes the truth behind Bettenou's agent, and Bettenou and Inga battle one more time.
